---

<Base
  title={title}
  description={metaDescription}
  canonical={canonical}
>
  <script slot="schema" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(localBusinessSchema)} />
  <script slot="schema" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(serviceSchema)} />

  <Header slot="header" />

  <div class="container py-6">
    <Breadcrumbs
      items={[
        { label: "Kitchen Fitter Nuneaton", href: "/kitchen-fitter-nuneaton/" },
      ]}
    />
  </div>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--bg-light);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-5 leading-tight" style="color: var(--navy);">
          Kitchen Fitter Nuneaton — Independent Installation by Pindi Sahota
        </h1>
        <AnswerBlock
          answer="Pindi Sahota is an independent kitchen fitter serving Nuneaton, Bedworth, and the surrounding north Warwickshire area. With 30 years of experience across CV10, CV11, CV12, and neighbouring postcodes, he fits kitchens from Wren, Howdens, Magnet, IKEA and every major retailer — with a fixed-price quote guaranteed after a £195 pre-installation survey (credited back on booking)."
        />
        <KeyTakeaway points={takeawayPoints} />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Photo Gallery -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6" style="color: var(--navy);">Kitchen Installations in Nuneaton</h2>
      <div class="gallery-grid">
        <figure class="gallery-figure">
          <img
            src="/assets/kitchen-fitter/kitchen-fitter-nuneaton-gloss-fitted-kitchen-warwickshire-4032x3024.webp"
            alt="Kitchen fitter Nuneaton — gloss fitted kitchen installation completed by Install My Kitchen in Warwickshire"
            width="4032"
            height="3024"
            loading="lazy"
            class="gallery-img"
          />
        </figure>
        <figure class="gallery-figure">
          <img
            src="/assets/kitchen-fitter/kitchen-fitter-nuneaton-white-gloss-granite-island-kitchen-3024x4032.webp"
            alt="Kitchen fitter Nuneaton — white gloss kitchen with granite island fitted in Nuneaton, Warwickshire"
            width="3024"
            height="4032"
            loading="lazy"
            class="gallery-img"
          />
        </figure>
        <figure class="gallery-figure">
          <img
            src="/assets/kitchen-fitter/kitchen-fitter-nuneaton-pindi-sahota-completed-installation-3024x4032.webp"
            alt="Pindi Sahota kitchen fitter Nuneaton — completed grey gloss kitchen installation in Warwickshire"
            width="3024"
            height="4032"
            loading="lazy"
            class="gallery-img"
          />
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 1: Independent vs Retailer Fitters -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--bg-light);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--navy);">
          Independent Kitchen Fitter vs Retailer Fitter — What's the Difference?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          When you buy a kitchen from a major retailer, installation is often offered as part of the package. In practice, retailer-scheme fitters are contractors working to the retailer's cost model and schedule — not to yours. If an issue arises, you are caught in the middle between a head office and a fitter already committed to their next job.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          An independent kitchen fitter like Pindi Sahota works directly for you. There is no conflict of interest, no incentive to minimise time on your job, and no call-centre layer between you and the person doing the work. Pindi visits your home in Nuneaton, surveys the room properly, produces a fixed-price quote based on actual site conditions — and then carries out every stage of the installation himself.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          This approach is particularly valuable in Nuneaton, where the housing stock presents a specific set of challenges. Many properties — post-war council-built homes now owner-occupied, 1960s–80s semis across Stockingford, Camp Hill, and Galley Common — have modest kitchen footprints, tight access through hallways and narrow doors, and older utility positions that do not always align with modern kitchen plans. These are situations where a templated, speed-optimised retailer fit frequently falls short. A survey-first, experienced independent fitter resolves these issues before work begins, not after completion.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Independent fitting also means complete retailer freedom. Pindi fits kitchens from any supplier, so you are free to shop at whichever retailer gives you the best kitchen for your budget.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Why Nuneaton Homeowners Choose Pindi -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--navy);">
          Why Nuneaton Homeowners Choose Pindi Sahota
        </h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Pindi Sahota has been fitting kitchens for 30 years and is based at 242 Hollyfast Road, Coundon, Coventry — approximately 10 miles south of Nuneaton town centre. He is a local tradesperson with genuine knowledge of Warwickshire's housing stock, not a franchise operative working from a central database.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Nuneaton is Warwickshire's largest town and its housing reflects successive waves of development. Near the town centre, Victorian terraces share streets with post-war council stock — both presenting the kinds of installation challenge that reward careful preparation: walls that are not plumb, floors that have been relaid multiple times, and kitchen footprints that do not leave much margin for error. Across Stockingford, Camp Hill, and Galley Common, the 1960s–80s semi-detached stock is solid and well-established but frequently has compact kitchens with appliance positions and window placements that require precise planning to work around.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Modern new-build estates at Bermuda Park and on Nuneaton's northern fringe bring a different set of considerations: tight construction tolerances, pre-fitted utilities in specific positions, and little room for ad hoc adjustment if the kitchen plan does not land exactly as specified. Getting this right requires the same careful survey process that serves Pindi's customers in every other property type.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Bedworth — immediately adjacent to Nuneaton across the CV12 postcode — is a closely linked community with a similar mix of housing and is fully covered as part of the same service area. Pindi has worked across both towns throughout his career.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Pindi also holds trade accounts with Howdens and Benchmarx, allowing him to source handles, fixings, and small components directly from local depots at trade price. This saves you money and avoids the delays that come with ordering replacements through a retailer's customer service line.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: The Survey-First Process -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--bg-light);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--navy);">
          The Survey-First Process — How It Works
        </h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Every kitchen fitting project begins with a pre-installation survey, carried out by Pindi personally at your Nuneaton or Bedworth home. The survey costs £195 and is credited back in full if you go ahead with the installation. It is a working appointment, not a sales visit — the outcome is a detailed, accurate quote for the specific job in your specific room.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          During the survey, Pindi takes precise measurements of the room, checks ceiling heights and wall angles, inspects existing plumbing and electrical routes, reviews your kitchen plan and elevation drawings, and identifies any preparatory work needed before or during installation. In Nuneaton's tighter-footprint properties this stage is especially important: tight access routes, low-clearance doorways, and restricted manoeuvrability for carcasses are all conditions that need to be planned around rather than discovered on fitting day.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Following the survey you receive a written, fixed-price quote. The price does not change unless you change the scope of work. There are no hidden charges on completion and no retrospective claims for complications that the survey should have — and did — identify in advance.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Survey appointments in Nuneaton are typically available within two weeks. Installation slots follow within four to eight weeks of the survey, depending on your preferred timeline. To book, call <a href="tel:07399651836" class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--teal);">07399 651836</a> or visit the <a href="/survey/" class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--teal);">survey booking page</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: Retailers -->
  <section class="section">
